<title>Concerning apparitions (or How, when the first wife of Dia!kwain was buried, those returning to their homes saw the apparition of a little child) </title>
<summary><i>Apparition seen by the party returning from the burial of the narrator’s wife; followed by the account of an apparition seen, on another occasion, by the narrator’s brother–in–law. In the Katkop dialect, by Díä!kwãin (L V.-22. 5810, 23. 5811-5832). </i>Dia!kwain and his people were returning from burying his wife when they saw an apparition that resembled Dia!kwain&apos;s wife. He believed it to be something that appears at the time when sorcerers take people away. Dia!kwain&apos;s brother-in-law, Mansse, also saw an apparition on the hunting-ground. Apparitions resemble people in some ways, but are also different.</summary><comments>1) p.5809v: &apos;A personal adventure – Related by Dia!kwain&apos;, 2) This story is found in Books V-22 and V-23</comments><date>3 January 1876 (started)</date><storypages>5810, 5811-5832</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>Dia!kwain (David Hoesar) (V)</author><keyword><kw>Dia!kwain</kw><subkw>his brother-in-law, Mansse</subkw></keyword>
